Renco Group Seeks to Restart Peru Smelter, Pay Debts in 4 Years

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-02-17T16:12:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/renco-group-seeks-to-restart-peru-smelter-pay-debts-in-4-years.html
Renco Group Inc. is ready to begin
talks with the Peruvian government to reopen its La Oroya zinc
and lead smelter, the company said today.  Renco can clean up past pollution at the site within 20
months and clear debts with concentrate suppliers within four
years, with the support of its partner Glencore International
AG, the New York-based company said today in a statement
published in Lima-based newspaper Gestion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  